SIMPLE: pressurize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: pressurize
<hw>pressurize</hw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To increase the pressure on (a
gas or liquid); <as>as, <ex>pressurized</ex> oxygen</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> supercharge, apply pressure to.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To increase and maintain a pressure in (a
compartment or container), above that of the ambient pressure; -- of
airplanes, space suits, and diving bells, for example; <as>as, the
airplane cabin was <ex>pressurized</ex> for the comfort of the
passengers</as>; the sterile room was <ex>pressurized</ex> to prevent
contamination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>negatively pressurized</b></col> <cd>maintained at a
pressure somewhat below that of ambient pressure; -- a technique
sometimes used to keep airborn materials in a room from escaping out;
<as>as, the biohazard lab was <ex>negatively pressurized</ex> to keep
hazardous biological agents from escaping into the
environment</as>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presswork</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Press work</ent>⟦br⟧
